text: Hurricane Kyle of 2002 was a very long-lived storm that began in September and lasted into October. This hurricane lasted almost a month. It was the fifth- longest Atlantic storm recorded. Toward the end of its life, Hurricane Kyle made landfall twice, once in eastern South Carolina and another in North Carolina. Hurricane Kyle caused almost $5,000,000 USD in damage. ==References== Category:2002 Atlantic hurricane season Category:Category 1 Atlantic hurricanes Category:Hurricanes in the United States
title: Hurricane Kyle (2002)
